## UI/UX Standards

### Tailwind CSS

- Use Tailwind utility classes exclusively. No inline `style` props.
- Use `clsx` + `tailwind-merge` for conditional or merged class names.
- Design tokens (colors, spacing) are defined in `tailwind.config.ts` — never hardcode hex values.

```tsx
import { clsx } from "clsx";
import { twMerge } from "tailwind-merge";

export function cn(...inputs: Parameters<typeof clsx>) {
  return twMerge(clsx(inputs));
}

// Usage
<button className={cn("px-4 py-2 rounded", isActive && "bg-green-600 text-white")} />
```

### Form Handling

- Use `react-hook-form` for forms. Validate with Zod schemas.
- Forms are controlled via `react-hook-form` — avoid manual `useState` for form fields.
- Disable submit buttons during submission (`isSubmitting`).
- Display field-level validation errors inline.

```tsx
import { useForm } from "react-hook-form";
import { zodResolver } from "@hookform/resolvers/zod";
import { z } from "zod";

const schema = z.object({
  notes: z.string().max(500).optional(),
  scheduledAt: z.string().min(1, "Date is required"),
});

type FormValues = z.infer<typeof schema>;

export function BookingForm({ onSubmit }: { onSubmit: (values: FormValues) => void }) {
  const { register, handleSubmit, formState: { errors, isSubmitting } } = useForm<FormValues>({
    resolver: zodResolver(schema),
  });

  return (
    <form onSubmit={handleSubmit(onSubmit)}>
      <input {...register("scheduledAt")} type="datetime-local" aria-label="Appointment date" />
      {errors.scheduledAt && <p className="text-red-500 text-sm">{errors.scheduledAt.message}</p>}
      <button type="submit" disabled={isSubmitting}>
        {isSubmitting ? "Saving..." : "Book"}
      </button>
    </form>
  );
}
```

### Navigation

- Use React Router `<Link>` and `useNavigate` for all navigation.
- Implement breadcrumb navigation on nested views.

### Accessibility

- All interactive elements have accessible labels (`aria-label` or visible label).
- Use semantic HTML: `<button>`, `<nav>`, `<main>`, `<section>`, `<article>`.
- Ensure keyboard navigability for all interactive components.
- Color contrast must meet WCAG AA (4.5:1 for normal text).
- Images have `alt` text. Decorative images use `alt=""`.

