## Testing Standards

### Unit and Component Tests

Use Vitest + React Testing Library. Test behavior, not implementation details.

```tsx
// tests/unit/AppointmentCard.test.tsx
import { render, screen, fireEvent } from "@testing-library/react";
import { describe, it, expect, vi } from "vitest";
import { AppointmentCard } from "@/features/appointments/components/AppointmentCard";

describe("AppointmentCard", () => {
  it("displays appointment date", () => {
    render(<AppointmentCard appointment={mockAppointment} onCancel={vi.fn()} />);
    expect(screen.getByText(mockAppointment.scheduledAt)).toBeInTheDocument();
  });

  it("calls onCancel with appointment id when cancel clicked", () => {
    const onCancel = vi.fn();
    render(<AppointmentCard appointment={mockAppointment} onCancel={onCancel} />);
    fireEvent.click(screen.getByRole("button", { name: /cancel/i }));
    expect(onCancel).toHaveBeenCalledWith(mockAppointment.id);
  });
});
```

### React Query Tests

Wrap components in a `QueryClientProvider` in tests.

```tsx
import { QueryClient, QueryClientProvider } from "@tanstack/react-query";
import { render } from "@testing-library/react";

function renderWithQuery(ui: React.ReactElement) {
  const client = new QueryClient({ defaultOptions: { queries: { retry: false } } });
  return render(<QueryClientProvider client={client}>{ui}</QueryClientProvider>);
}
```

### API Mocking

Use MSW to mock API calls in tests. Define handlers in `tests/mocks/handlers.ts`.

```ts
// tests/mocks/handlers.ts
import { http, HttpResponse } from "msw";

export const handlers = [
  http.get("/api/v1/appointments", () => {
    return HttpResponse.json({ data: [mockAppointment] });
  }),
];
```

### Test Naming Convention

- `<ComponentName>.test.tsx` for component tests.
- `use<Name>.test.ts` for hook tests.
- Test descriptions follow: `"<verb>s <subject> when <condition>"`
  - e.g., `"displays loading spinner when data is fetching"`, `"calls onCancel when button clicked"`

### Test Coverage

- **Threshold**: 80% lines and branches for frontend.
- Run: `vitest run --coverage`

### Definition of Done — Frontend

- [ ] TypeScript compiles without errors (`tsc --noEmit`)
- [ ] ESLint passes (`eslint src/`)
- [ ] All Vitest tests pass (`vitest run`)
- [ ] Coverage ≥ 80% (`vitest run --coverage`)
- [ ] Component is accessible (semantic HTML, aria labels, keyboard navigable)
- [ ] Loading and error states are handled and rendered
- [ ] No inline styles — Tailwind classes only
- [ ] All new API integrations use React Query hooks

